records.addlTxt:
Defendant Sirmilton Freeman in court with attorney Richard J. Carpenter.  Erin M. Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for sentencing hearing. Parties are prepared to proceed. Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Tracy B. ADA Jesica Ballenger appeared on behalf of ADA Erin Karshen after defense counsel's statements as ADA Karshen is needed for a jury trial in Branch 10. 

As to COUNT 1 as AMENDED:
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to COUNTS 2 & 3 as AMENDED; credit for 3 days time served. Court will allow work release ONLY if defendant is employed at the time of revocation.

As to COUNT 2 as AMENDED:
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to COUNTS 1 & 3 as AMENDED; credit for 3 days time served. Court will allow work release ONLY if defendant is employed at the time of revocation.

As to COUNT 3 as AMENDED:
Court ordered defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent to COUNTS 1 & 2 as AMENDED; credit for 3 days time served. Court will allow work release ONLY if defendant is employed at the time of revocation.

If revoked, court costs, fees and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds.

Court STAYED the sentence on COUNTS 1 AMENDED, 2 AMENDED & 3 AMENDED and placed defendant on probation for 30 MONTHS with the following conditions:

1) Complete 80 hours of community service at an agency that is pre-approved by the agent;
2) AODA assessment and comply with any recommended treatment and counseling;
3) No contact with the victim;
4) Pay all costs, fees and surcharges during period of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
5) Obtain/maintain full time employment. If defendant is not employed full time, he must be employed part time and enrolled in school part time.
6) Participate in vocational training;
7) Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge. Court WAIVED DNA surcharge on COUNTS 2 and 3 as AMENDED as they are part of a continuous event; 
8) Maintain absolute sobriety;

Court will defer ruling on sex offender registration until the probation review hearing date. 

Court ordered a probation review hearing be set.  AODA agency to prepare a report regarding the defendants progress on probation for the next court date. 

Defendant to prepare a letter for the Court that discusses the consequences of his behavior on the victim, on his family and others, and what he has learned from his behavior.  

Probation Review Hearing scheduled for July 22, 2015 at 8:30 a.m. in Branch 25. 

Appellate rights notice given to the defendant. 
Filed;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
